SIMPLE: weighty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weighty
<hw>Weight"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Weightier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Weightiest</adjf>.]</amorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Having weight; heavy; ponderous; <as>as, a
<ex>weighty</ex> body</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Adapted to turn the balance in the mind, or to
convince; important; forcible; serious; momentous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧For
sundry <xex>weighty</xex> reasons.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let me have your advice in a <qex>weighty</qex> affair.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Rigorous; severe; afflictive.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Attend our <xex>weightier</xex>
judgment.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Heavy; ponderous; burdensome; onerous; forcible;
momentous; efficacious; impressive; cogent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weil's disease</ent>⟦br⟧
